Samples%20Of%20MDH%20And%20Everest%20Spice%20Mixes%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESingapore%2C%20last%20week%2C%C2%A0%20took%20action%20against%20Everest%20Food%20Products%20Pvt.%2C%20banning%20the%20sale%20of%20its%20products%20citing%20alleged%20detection%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%20at%20levels%20surpassing%20permissible%20limits.%20Following%20suit%2C%20Hong%20Kong%20has%20also%20prohibited%20the%20sale%20of%20popular%20Indian%20spice%20brands%20MDH%20Pvt.%20and%20Everest%20Food%20Products%20Pvt.%20after%20reported%20findings%20of%20the%20carcinogenic%20pesticide%20in%20several%20spice%20mixes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20ethylene%20oxide%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EEthylene%20oxide%20is%20a%20chemical%20compound%20with%20the%20formula%20C2H4O.%20It%20is%20a%20flammable%2C%20colourless%20gas%20with%20a%20sweet%20odour%20at%20room%20temperature.%20It%20is%20an%20effective%20sterilising%20agent%20due%20to%20its%20ability%20to%20damage%20DNA.%20But%20this%20very%20same%20quality%20of%20the%20compound%20also%20lends%20ethylene%20oxide%20its%20carcinogenic%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhat%20are%20the%20uses%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20USA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cancer.gov%2Fabout-cancer%2Fcauses-prevention%2Frisk%2Fsubstances%2Fethylene-oxide%5C%22%3ENational%20Cancer%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20used%20primarily%20to%20produce%20other%20chemicals%2C%20including%20antifreeze.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20also%20a%20chemical%20intermediate%20in%20the%20manufacture%20of%20ethylene%20glycol.%20Due%20to%20its%20properties%2C%20it%20is%20used%20as%20a%20sterilising%20agent%20for%20medical%20equipment%20and%20a%20fumigating%20agent%20for%20spices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhy%20is%20ethylene%20oxide%20harmful%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2016-09%2Fdocuments%2Fethylene-oxide.pdf%5C%22%3EThe%20International%20Agency%20For%20Research%20on%20Cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ethylene%20oxide%20is%20a%20Group%201%20carcinogenic%2C%20which%20means%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20enough%20evidence%20to%20conclude%20that%20it%20can%20cause%20cancer%20in%20humans.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20Ethylene%20oxide%20enters%20the%20human%20body%20through%20inhalation%20and%20ingestion.%C2%A0%20As%20per%20the%20U.S.%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%2C%20%E2%80%9Cexposure%20to%20ethylene%20oxide%20increases%20the%20risk%20of%20lymphoid%20cancer%20and%2C%20for%20females%2C%20breast%20cancer.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAdditionally%2C%20prolonged%20use%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%20can%20adversely%20affect%20the%20human%20body%2C%20Short-term%20effects%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%20include%20%E2%80%9Ccentral%20nervous%20system%20depression%20and%20irritation%20of%20the%20eyes%20and%20mucous%20membranes%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20long-term%20exposure%20can%20cause%20%E2%80%9Cirritation%20of%20the%20eyes%2C%20skin%2C%20nose%2C%20throat%2C%20and%20lungs%2C%20and%20damage%20to%20the%20brain%20and%20nervous%20system%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhat%20Singapore%2C%20Hong%20Kong%20said%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sfa.gov.sg%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Faccredited-overseas-attachments%2F180424-media-release---recall-of-everest%2527s-masala-fish-curry.pdf%3Fsfvrsn%3De0a4f694_1%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Singapore%20stated%20%E2%80%9Cethylene%20oxide%20is%20allowed%20to%20be%20used%20in%20the%20sterilisation%20of%20spices%E2%80%9D%20but%20added%20that%20%E2%80%9Dexposure%20to%20this%20substance%20should%20be%20minimised%20as%20much%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CAlthough%20there%20is%20no%20immediate%20risk%20to%20consumption%20of%20food%20contaminated%20with%20low%20levels%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%2C%20long%20term%20exposure%20may%20lead%20to%20health%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cethylene%20oxide%20is%20a%20pesticide%20that%20is%20not%20authorised%20for%20use%20in%20food%E2%80%9D%20in%20Singapore%20and%20can%20be%20%E2%80%9Cused%20to%20fumigate%20agricultural%20products%20to%20prevent%20microbial%20contamination.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfs.gov.hk%2Fenglish%2Fpress%2F20240405_10919.html%5C%22%3EHong%20Kong's%20Centre%20for%20Food%20Safety%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20about%20the%20spices%3A%20%E2%80%9C%20The%20test%20results%20showed%20that%20the%20samples%20contained%20a%20pesticide%2C%20ethylene%20oxide%E2%80%A6%20The%20International%20Agency%20for%20Research%20on%20Cancer%20has%20classified%20ethylene%20oxide%20as%20a%20Group%201%20carcinogen%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20instructed%20vendors%20to%20stop%20sale%20of%20the%20affected%20products.%20They%20have%20withdrawn%20MDH's%20Madras%20Curry%20Powder%2C%20Sambhar%20Masala%20Powder%2C%20Curry%20Powder%20and%20Everest's%20Fish%20Curry%20Masala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFollowing%20the%20move%2C%20the%20commerce%20ministry%20has%20directed%20Indian%20embassies%20in%20both%20Singapore%20and%20Hong%20Kong%20to%20send%20a%20detailed%20report%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713938220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fbtqj1nk8_mdh-everest-masala-_625x300_22_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwhat-is-ethylene-oxide-found-in-samples-of-mdh-and-everest-spice-mixes-5510812%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Singapore%2C%20last%20week%2C%20took%20action%20against%20Everest%20Food%20Products%20Pvt.%2C%20banning%20the%20sale%20of%20its%20products%20citing%20alleged%20detection%20of%20ethylene%20oxide%20at%20levels%20surpassing%20permissible%20limits.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%2